{"title":"Workshop 03 - Data Analysis in R","markdown":{"yaml":{"title":"Workshop 03 - Data Analysis in R","subtitle":"Tidyverse Workflows for Biodiversity Data","author":"Maria Lopez","date":"2024-09-01","format":{"revealjs":{"theme":"default","slide-number":true,"footer":"ARBO-WATCH — Workshop 03"}}},"headingText":"Overview","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n\n- Introduction to the tidyverse\n- Cleaning and wrangling field data\n- Visualising biodiversity patterns with ggplot2\n\n---\n\n## The Tidyverse\n\n- A collection of R packages designed for data science\n- Consistent grammar: `dplyr`, `tidyr`, `ggplot2`, `readr`\n- Pipe-based workflows: `|>`\n\n---\n\n## Data Cleaning\n\n```{.r}\ndf_clean <- df |>\n  drop_na(species, count) |>\n  filter(count > 0) |>\n  mutate(date = as.Date(date))\n```\n\n- Remove rows with missing critical values\n- Filter out invalid records\n- Parse dates correctly\n\n---\n\n## Data Wrangling\n\n```{.r}\nspecies_summary <- df_clean |>\n  group_by(species) |>\n  summarise(\n    total_count = sum(count),\n    n_sites = n_distinct(site),\n    .groups = \"drop\"\n  )\n```\n\n- Aggregate counts per species\n- Count number of distinct sites per species\n\n---\n\n## Visualisation\n\n```{.r}\nspecies_summary |>\n  slice_max(total_count, n = 10) |>\n  ggplot(aes(x = reorder(species, total_count), y = total_count)) +\n  geom_col(fill = \"#2E7D32\") +\n  coord_flip() +\n  theme_minimal()\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n- Tidyverse provides a consistent, readable workflow\n- Always inspect and clean data before analysis\n- ggplot2 makes it easy to produce publication-quality figures\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":"\n\n## Overview\n\n- Introduction to the tidyverse\n- Cleaning and wrangling field data\n- Visualising biodiversity patterns with ggplot2\n\n---\n\n## The Tidyverse\n\n- A collection of R packages designed for data science\n- Consistent grammar: `dplyr`, `tidyr`, `ggplot2`, `readr`\n- Pipe-based workflows: `|>`\n\n---\n\n## Data Cleaning\n\n```{.r}\ndf_clean <- df |>\n  drop_na(species, count) |>\n  filter(count > 0) |>\n  mutate(date = as.Date(date))\n```\n\n- Remove rows with missing critical values\n- Filter out invalid records\n- Parse dates correctly\n\n---\n\n## Data Wrangling\n\n```{.r}\nspecies_summary <- df_clean |>\n  group_by(species) |>\n  summarise(\n    total_count = sum(count),\n    n_sites = n_distinct(site),\n    .groups = \"drop\"\n  )\n```\n\n- Aggregate counts per species\n- Count number of distinct sites per species\n\n---\n\n## Visualisation\n\n```{.r}\nspecies_summary |>\n  slice_max(total_count, n = 10) |>\n  ggplot(aes(x = reorder(species, total_count), y = total_count)) +\n  geom_col(fill = \"#2E7D32\") +\n  coord_flip() +\n  theme_minimal()\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n- Tidyverse provides a consistent, readable workflow\n- Always inspect and clean data before analysis\n- ggplot2 makes it easy to produce publication-quality figures\n"},"formats":{"revealjs":{"identifier":{"display-name":"RevealJS","target-format":"revealjs","base-format":"revealjs"},"execute":{"fig-width":10,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":false,"output":true,"warning":false,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"markdown"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":"none","code-overflow":"scroll","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":true,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":1,"latex-max-runs":10,"latex-makeindex":"makeindex","l